parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause loss of control, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel is hard to turn
the steering wheel is stiff
the vehicle pulls to one side
the vehicle is difficult to control
the vehicle jerks or swerves while driving
unusual noises while steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the engine to stall, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine stalls while driving
the vehicle loses power
the fuel pump makes unusual noises
the check engine light is on
the vehicle is difficult to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the O2 sensor can cause poor engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and increased emissions, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The check engine light is on
the vehicle is difficult to start
the vehicle runs rough
the vehicle has poor fuel efficiency.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of fuel system components can cause fuel leaks, engine stalling, and difficulty starting the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Fuel smell
fuel leaks
difficulty starting the vehicle
engine stalling
corrosion on fuel pump connector and sending unit.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall, making it difficult or impossible to continue driving, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle stalling
difficulty starting the vehicle
fuel smell
fuel leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Inlet Shutter Valve Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the fuel tank inlet shutter valve can cause fuel to backwash out of the fuel filler, resulting in fuel spills and potential fires.
symptoms: Fuel backwashing out of the fuel filler
fuel spills.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Repair of Fuel System Components
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate repair of fuel system components can cause the problems to persist, leading to continued safety risks and financial losses for the vehicle owner.
symptoms: Continued fuel leaks
engine stalling
and difficulty starting the vehicle after repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure and Anti-Lock Braking System (ABS) Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes and ABS can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, as the vehicle may not stop or slow down as expected.
symptoms: The brakes may lock abnormally
the brake pedal may feel soft or spongy
the brake pedal may stick to the floor
the ABS light may illuminate on the instrument panel
the vehicle may not stop or slow down as expected
the brakes may fail to engage
and the vehicle may experience unusual noises or smells.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in a crash can increase the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag may not deploy in a crash
the airbag may deploy incorrectly
and the airbag may not deploy at all.
